> how can I test the execution time to create a timeout test and ensure the code is optimized?
You can write a code and run it in the IDE mode to see what the time limit is for each programming language, e.g. something like this in C#:

using System;
class Solution {
    static void Main(string[] args) {
        string operation = Console.ReadLine();
        int key = int.Parse(Console.ReadLine());
        string message = Console.ReadLine();
        DateTime start_time = DateTime.UtcNow;
        while (true) {
            DateTime end_time = DateTime.UtcNow;
            TimeSpan timeDiff = end_time - start_time;
            Console.Error.WriteLine(timeDiff);
        }
    }
}

Please notice that the time limits are different for different languages. Please do not make cases where it would be impossible to solve in the slower languages.

